{
  "text": "The aim of this study is to explore the impact of divergent natural selection in different types of range margins by comparing indirect estimates of gene flow and genome scans for signature of selection between these trailing-edge and leading-edge populations. According to the hypothesis of [CITATION_1] postulating selection for local adaptation in areas with little climate-enforced range shifts, a clear signature of selection in the trailing-edge population and none or only a low one in the leading-edge population is expected.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "86278653"
  },
